@tgravescs
Manual testing was done by standing up a single-node kafka server and using the console producer to send events to it. The buffer size was set very low to ensure that it would be exhausted. 

The setting seemed to work properly. When blocking was enabled, the producer paused until a buffer was freed, and when it was disabled the producer died with the expected exception.

